12/12/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- President Fatmir Sejdiu on Tuesday (December 11th) authorised Hashim Thaci, whose Democratic Party of Kosovo (DPK) won the November 17th elections, to form the province's next government. 
The DPK won 37 seats, followed by Sejdiu's Democratic League of Kosovo, with 25 seats. 
Together they will have a majority of 62 seats in the 120-seat parliament. 
The new government is expected to be announced by the end of December and to receive a vote of confidence in parliament in early January. 
(Kosovalive, RTK, Kosovapress, RFE, Reuters, Xinhua - 12/12/07; Reuters, DPA, Xinhua, AFP - 11/12/07)
